{
  "texts": [
    "A similar trend was observed in the math reasoning subset, where the Qwen3-4B model, for example, saw its XParaCon score improve from 4.489 to 4.856.",
    "This fine-tuned robustness, particularly for Qwen3-4B, reached a level comparable to, or exceeding, several much larger open-source models, underscoring the power of goal-oriented supervised fine-tuning.",
    "10 Figures 3 and 4 provide a comprehensive view of the XParaCon scores for each model.",
    "However, it is noteworthy that for the Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct model on the math reasoning subset, this significant boost in XParaCon was accompanied by a minor decline in raw accuracy, lighting the possibility of a potential trade-off between consistency and correctness in domain-specific tasks for light-weighted models.",
    "Alting von Geusau and Bloem (2021) evaluate QA robustness to paraphrased questions, finding consistent performance drops and showing BERT's sentence embeddings better capture paraphrase similarity than alternatives."
  ]
}